import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Penicillin'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Penicillin Effectiveness')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin effectiveness across all bacteria species?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Neomycin'].plot.hist()
    plt.xlabel('Neomycin Effectiveness')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax = plt.gca()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    median_effectiveness = data['Neomycin'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_effectiveness, color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {median_effectiveness:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Neomycin effectiveness across all bacteria species?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
